datafaq.sual: What is TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: TamKart is a multifunctional card provided by ABB that allows you to manage two different accounts on one card.

datafaq.sual: Is credit cashback available on TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: On the credit side of TamKart with POS and e-commerce, ABB provides a minimum of 2% cashback, and with POS and e-commerce of other banks - 1%. A minimum of 2% cashback is set on the debit side. When cashback , provided by QayğıCash Club partner stores, is more than 3%, the percentage of QayğıCash Club cashback is returned to the client. The percentage of cashback provided by the partner companies of the bank is indicated on the website

datafaq.sual: When will cashback be credited to the card?
datafaq.cavab: Cashback amounts provided by the bank are credited to the client's card by the last business day of the month. Cashback provided by QayğıCash Club partner stores is calculated immediately during the operation and credited to the client's card.

datafaq.sual: Where can I use TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: You can make POS payments worldwide, make online payments, and withdraw cash from ATMs.

datafaq.sual: How much of my TamKart credit limit can I use for cash?
datafaq.cavab: Depending on the type of card, there are monthly limits on the use for cash purposes (cash withdrawals from ATMs, C2C, cash by code, credit payments, etc.). The limit is updated monthly.

datafaq.sual: What are the cash target limits for different TamKart types?
datafaq.cavab: TamKart Classic/Standard card - 50%, TamKart Visa/MasterCard Gold card - 60%, TamKart Platinum card - 80% of the credit limit has a monthly limit for cash purposes. TamKart Premium cards have no limits .

datafaq.sual: Are there any restrictions when using the TamKart credit line for installment transactions or cashless payments?
datafaq.cavab: No, there are no restrictions on installment transactions or cashless payments using the TamKart credit line.

datafaq.sual: Can I pay another bank's loan with TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: Yes, but paying with TamKart credit will incur a 1.5% fee, minimum 2 AZN. There is no additional fee when using the debit side of TamKart.

datafaq.sual: How will my credit limit be determined?
datafaq.cavab: When applying to TamKart, a loan specialist will analyze your monthly income and expenses. After a preliminary analysis, you will be provided with information about the limit. The limit can be from 300 to 15,000 manat, depending on your income and credit limit.

datafaq.sual: Who can get TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: Anyone who receives a salary or pension using ABB cards, as well as persons who receive a salary using cards issued by other banks (employees of public institutions served from the state budget, or employees of enterprises operating in the oil and gas industry). The provision of the card is determined on the basis of a preliminary analysis by a credit specialist.

datafaq.sual: How can I get TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: You can order TamKart online from the site
datafaq.cavab2: or get it at the nearest ABB branches. To order TamKart Debit cards, you can place an order on the website

datafaq.sual: Can I get TamKart if I have a loan from another bank?
datafaq.cavab: Yes, but a loan officer will determine if a parallel loan is eligible based on an analysis of your income and expenses.

datafaq.sual: What is the validity period of TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: TamKart is officially valid for up to 60 months. TamKart credit line is valid for 3 to 6 months.

datafaq.sual: How is an installment transaction calculated using TamKart?
datafaq.cavab: With TamKart, you can purchase any product in partner stores and pay for it in installments. The amount of expenses is divided into 3, 6, 12, 18 or 24 months and paid in equal installments.

datafaq.sual: How is debt calculated when using a TamKart line of credit?
datafaq.cavab: When using a credit line, a grace period will apply until the 10th day of the next month, and the debt must be fully paid by the 10th day of the next month. For all non-urgent transactions made over 20 AZN domestically and abroad, the grace period is applied 30 to 60 days.

datafaq.sual: What happens if the debt is not paid within the grace period?
datafaq.cavab: In case of debt not exceeding 20 AZN, used with a credit line, a penalty is applied in accordance with the annual rate. For unpaid debt during the grace period, an annual rate of up to 18 months will be charged, paid in equal installments from 1 to 10 of the next months.

datafaq.sual: How can I find out the amount of my monthly payments?
datafaq.cavab: Information about TamKart (your balance, stores where you have made purchases, amounts you have to pay, payment schedule, etc.) you can get on the site
datafaq.cavab3: . To do this, you must enter your ID pin, the last 4 digits of the card and mobile number. Then enter the one-time password that comes to your registered mobile number.

datafaq.sual: How can I pay my debt on TamKart?
datafaq.def: You can pay your debt on TamKart in the following ways:
datafaq.Abbmobile: via the ABB mobile app, card-to-card transfer;

datafaq.sual: When do I have to pay monthly payments?
datafaq.cavab: Monthly payments must be made between the 1st and 10th of each month.

datafaq.sual: What happens if I don't pay my TamKart debt on time?
datafaq.cavab: In this case, your credit card may be blocked. If there are delays with TamKart, your credit history will reflect delays and a penalty rate will be charged on the overdue amount.

datafaq.sual: Can I increase or decrease my TamKart credit limit?
datafaq.cavab: In order to decrease or increase the TamKart credit limit, you need to contact the bank. Increasing the TamKart credit limit is possible depending on the use of the card. To do this, you must use the card for several months and pay the payments on time.

datafaq.sual: What happens if a payment falls on a non-working day?
datafaq.cavab: If a payment falls on a non-business day, it will be credited to your account on the next business day. Therefore, it is recommended that you pay payments that fall on a non-business day one business day in advance during business hours.

datafaq.sual: What is Lounge Key?
